column2: The best investment you can make is in yourself. That and titanium alloys used to make micro-lasers.
Real estate and technology are always a smart investment. I own half the world's volcanoes and weather machines.
Successful habits breed successful people. I also breed them in my lab.
Surround yourself with smart people who's ideas you'll be able to steal.
Failure is not final if you have the technology to wipe clean the memory of anyone who witnessed your failure.
Your career is like a tree that will grow and grow. Cut down surrounding trees so it has more sunlight.
Success has to be nurtured and fed like a hungry baby...and this baby is hungry for blood, not applesauce
Give a man a fish and he'll eat for a day. Teach him to make great viral content and his social media reach will live forever.
Fake it until you make it - in business and in human compassion.
If you don't like the music on the radio, buy up all the record labels and make them put out something better.
You need balance in life, that's why I only go to work on days that end in 'y.'
Once you unleash your potential, use it to eviscerate the people who leashed it in the first place.
If you can't stand the heat, get out of the kitchen that I've been warming slowly over the last few hours.
Fight fire with fire. Fight social media rivals with superior viral content.
Every cloud has a silver lining so I've developed superior cloud-mining technologies.
Anyone who says 'more money, more problems' clearly doesn't have enough money.
If you're ever drawing a blank, reload your idea gun with hollowpoint bullets.
Cut to the chase, every moment I listen to you is a moment I'm not swimming in my skypool.
Employees: You must be willing to give an arm and a leg to succeed. Leave them with my secretary.
